Not saying Messi is wrong here, but the outcome would be a different story had it been Ronaldo instead of Messi.


Messi is more likable as a person compare to CR7 who can be arrogant at time, but Messi fanboys (including many sports commentators) are worse than ronaldo fanboys when it comes to stupidity, jealousy and hate.

snippet.textDisplay:
Messi is fed up with everyone pointing the finger at him his mates and Valverde.
I thought this was weird too because Messi almost never gives his opinion on things.
I think he wanted to send a literal message to Barcelona’s fans, board, President etc.
He’s didn’t say this to threaten the board, he said this to shed light on why Barcelona is suffering the way it is.
Yes the players and coach on the field are to blame but the board and sporting director chose these players to represent the club.
He’s not leaving, but if things don’t get better I do see him retiring.
He’s said it himself, he’s aware of his age and knows retirement is inevitable. It’s part of football.
He won’t move to another club, he’ll simply retire. And most likely start his coaching career shortly after.
